	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: (Mockup) Labyrinth Zone</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If the program leaves rendering turned off just before the start of the first line of picture, the pattern is different. Battletoads turns rendering on late to increase usable video memory bandwidth on NTSC. I do the same in my <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=94658#p94658" class="postlink">rgb121 demo</a> to keep the phase pattern from destructively interfering with dithering. But it does create a bit more of a moving texture overlaying the picture, as  infiniteneslives pointed out: &quot;The 'motion' is difficult to ignore&quot;.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


